```yaml
configuration:
  name:
    type: dynamic
  obsLinkName:
    type: dynamic
  obsInputBucket:
    type: dynamic
  obsOutputBucket:
    type: dynamic
  obsLinkNameInput:
    type: dynamic
resources:
  input:
    type: huaweicloud:Obs:Bucket
    properties:
      bucket: job-input
      acl: private
      forceDestroy: true
  output:
    type: huaweicloud:Obs:Bucket
    properties:
      bucket: job-output
      acl: private
      forceDestroy: true
  test:
    type: huaweicloud:Cdm:Job
    properties:
      jobType: NORMAL_JOB
      clusterId: ${huaweicloud_cdm_cluster.test.id}
      sourceConnector: obs-connector
      sourceLinkName: ${obsLinkName}
      sourceConfig:
        bucketName: ${obsInputBucket}
        inputDirectory: /
        listTextFile: false
        inputFormat: BINARY_FILE
        fromCompression: NONE
        fromFileOpType: DO_NOTHING
        useMarkerFile: false
        useTimeFilter: false
        fileSeparator: '|'
        filterType: NONE
        useWildCard: false
        decryption: NONE
        nonexistentPathDisregard: false
      destinationConnector: obs-connector
      destinationLinkName: ${obsLinkName}
      destinationJobConfig:
        bucketName: ${obsOutputBucket}
        outputDirectory: /
        outputFormat: BINARY_FILE
        validateMD5: true
        recordMD5Result: false
        duplicateFileOpType: REPLACE
        useCustomDirectory: false
        encryption: NONE
        copyContentType: false
        shouldClearTable: false
      config:
        retryType: NONE
        schedulerEnabled: false
        throttlingExtractorsNumber: 4
        throttlingRecordDirtyData: false
        throttlingMaxErrorRecords: 10
        throttlingLoaderNumber: 1
```

## Supporting Types



<h4 id="jobconfig">Job<wbr>Config</h4>

<div>
<pulumi-choosable type="language" values="csharp">
<dl class="resources-properties"><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="groupname_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#groupname_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Group<wbr>Name</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies group to which a job belongs. The default group is <code>DEFAULT</code>.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="retrytype_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#retrytype_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Retry<wbr>Type</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies whether to automatically retry if a job fails to be executed.
The options are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>NONE</strong>: Do not retry.</li>
<li><strong>RETRY_TRIPLE</strong>: Retry three times.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulercycle_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulercycle_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Scheduler<wbr>Cycle</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">int</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies cycle of a scheduled task. If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to minute
and <code>scheduler_cycle</code> is set to 10, the scheduled task is executed every 10 minutes.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulercycletype_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulercycletype_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Scheduler<wbr>Cycle<wbr>Type</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies cycle type of a scheduled task. The options are as follows:
<code>minute</code>, <code>hour</code>, <code>day</code>, <code>week</code>, <code>month</code>.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulerdisposabletype_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulerdisposabletype_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Scheduler<wbr>Disposable<wbr>Type</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies whether to delete a job after the job is executed.
The options are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>NONE</strong>: The job will not be deleted after it is executed.</li>
<li><strong>DELETE_AFTER_SUCCEED</strong>: The job will be deleted only after it is successfully executed. It is applicable to
massive one-time jobs.</li>
<li><strong>DELETE</strong>: Thejob will be deleted after it is executed, regardless of the execution result.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulerenabled_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulerenabled_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Scheduler<wbr>Enabled</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">bool</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies whether to enable a scheduled task.  Default value is <code>false</code>.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulerrunat_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulerrunat_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Scheduler<wbr>Run<wbr>At</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies time when a scheduled task is triggered in a cycle. This parameter
is valid only when <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to <code>hour</code>, <code>week</code>, or <code>month</code>.</p>
<ul>
<li>If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to month, cycle is set to 1, and runAt is set to 15, the scheduled task is executed
on the 15th day of each month. You can set runAt to multiple values and separate the values with commas (,).
For example, if runAt is set to 1,2,3,4,5, the scheduled task is executed on the first day, second day, third day,
fourth day, and fifth day of each month.</li>
<li>If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to week and runAt is set to mon,tue,wed,thu,fri, the scheduled task is executed on
Monday to Friday.</li>
<li>If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to hour and runAt is set to 27,57, the scheduled task is executed at the 27th and
57th minute in the cycle.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulerstartdate_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulerstartdate_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Scheduler<wbr>Start<wbr>Date</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies start time of a scheduled task.
For example, <code>2018-01-24 19:56:19</code></p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulerstopdate_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulerstopdate_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Scheduler<wbr>Stop<wbr>Date</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies End time of a scheduled task. For example, <code>2018-01-27 23:59:00</code>.
If you do not set the end time, the scheduled task is always executed and will never stop.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="throttlingdirtywritetobucket_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#throttlingdirtywritetobucket_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Throttling<wbr>Dirty<wbr>Write<wbr>To<wbr>Bucket</a>

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>

</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="throttlingdirtywritetolink_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#throttlingdirtywritetolink_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Throttling<wbr>Dirty<wbr>Write<wbr>To<wbr>Link</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>

    </dt>

        <span class="property-type">String</span>

The options are as follows:</p>

<li><strong>RETRY_TRIPLE</strong>: Retry three times.</li>
</ul>

        <span id="schedulercycle_java">

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">Integer</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies cycle of a scheduled task. If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to minute
and <code>scheduler_cycle</code> is set to 10, the scheduled task is executed every 10 minutes.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulercycletype_java">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulercycletype_java" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">scheduler<wbr>Cycle<wbr>Type</a>

</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulerdisposabletype_java">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulerdisposabletype_java" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">scheduler<wbr>Disposable<wbr>Type</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies whether to delete a job after the job is executed.
The options are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>NONE</strong>: The job will not be deleted after it is executed.</li>
<li><strong>DELETE_AFTER_SUCCEED</strong>: The job will be deleted only after it is successfully executed. It is applicable to
massive one-time jobs.</li>
<li><strong>DELETE</strong>: Thejob will be deleted after it is executed, regardless of the execution result.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulerenabled_java">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulerenabled_java" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">scheduler<wbr>Enabled</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">Boolean</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies whether to enable a scheduled task.  Default value is <code>false</code>.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="schedulerrunat_java">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#schedulerrunat_java" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">scheduler<wbr>Run<wbr>At</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies time when a scheduled task is triggered in a cycle. This parameter
is valid only when <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to <code>hour</code>, <code>week</code>, or <code>month</code>.</p>
<ul>
<li>If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to month, cycle is set to 1, and runAt is set to 15, the scheduled task is executed
on the 15th day of each month. You can set runAt to multiple values and separate the values with commas (,).
For example, if runAt is set to 1,2,3,4,5, the scheduled task is executed on the first day, second day, third day,
fourth day, and fifth day of each month.</li>
<li>If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to week and runAt is set to mon,tue,wed,thu,fri, the scheduled task is executed on
Monday to Friday.</li>
<li>If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to hour and runAt is set to 27,57, the scheduled task is executed at the 27th and
57th minute in the cycle.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"

            title="Optional">
        <span id="scheduler_cycle_type_python">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#scheduler_cycle_type_python" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">scheduler_<wbr>cycle_<wbr>type</a>

            title="Optional">
        <span id="scheduler_disposable_type_python">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#scheduler_disposable_type_python" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">scheduler_<wbr>disposable_<wbr>type</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">str</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies whether to delete a job after the job is executed.
The options are as follows:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>NONE</strong>: The job will not be deleted after it is executed.</li>
<li><strong>DELETE_AFTER_SUCCEED</strong>: The job will be deleted only after it is successfully executed. It is applicable to
massive one-time jobs.</li>
<li><strong>DELETE</strong>: Thejob will be deleted after it is executed, regardless of the execution result.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="scheduler_enabled_python">

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">bool</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies whether to enable a scheduled task.  Default value is <code>false</code>.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="scheduler_run_at_python">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#scheduler_run_at_python" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">scheduler_<wbr>run_<wbr>at</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">str</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Specifies time when a scheduled task is triggered in a cycle. This parameter
is valid only when <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to <code>hour</code>, <code>week</code>, or <code>month</code>.</p>
<ul>
<li>If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to month, cycle is set to 1, and runAt is set to 15, the scheduled task is executed
on the 15th day of each month. You can set runAt to multiple values and separate the values with commas (,).
For example, if runAt is set to 1,2,3,4,5, the scheduled task is executed on the first day, second day, third day,
fourth day, and fifth day of each month.</li>
<li>If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to week and runAt is set to mon,tue,wed,thu,fri, the scheduled task is executed on
Monday to Friday.</li>
<li>If <code>scheduler_cycle_type</code> is set to hour and runAt is set to 27,57, the scheduled task is executed at the 27th and
57th minute in the cycle.</li>
</ul>
</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">

## Import



Jobs can be imported by `id`. It is composed of the ID of CDM cluster which this job run in and the name of job,

separated by a slash. For example,

```sh
 $ pulumi import huaweicloud:Cdm/job:Job test b11b407c-e604-4e8d-8bc4-92398320b847/jobName
```
